API Reference
Introduction
Operations
Controls
  • Get the list of controls available by the current user. GET: api/Controls
Elements
  • Gets the elements in the survey. GET: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/Elements
  • Gets an element in the survey. GET: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/Elements/{elementId}
  • Updates a element from a given survey by specifying by its unique identfier and with the specified input values. PUT: api/Surveys/5/Elements/2
  • Delete an element from a given survey by specifying by its unique identfier. DELETE: api/Surveys/5/Elements/2
  • Gets the elements associated with a question. GET: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/Elements/ContainsQuestion/{questionId}
  • Creates a new element in a given survey. POST: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/elements/New
  • Moves an element in the survey. PUT: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/Elements/Move
Languages
  • Gets the known languages. GET: api/Languages
  • Gets a known language. GET: api/Languages/{languageId}
PageTemplates
  • Get the list of page templates available by the current user. GET: api/PageTemplates
Preferences
  • Gets the settings of the current user. GET: api/Preferences
  • Updates the settings of the current user. PUT: api/Preferences
Preview
  • GET /api/Preview
  • Gets HTML preview for the page containing a specified question. GET: api/Preview?surveyId=1questionId=99
Publish
  • Publishes a survey to the first CcaWebApi server (ordered by Id) associated with the user. POST: api/survey/{surveyId}/Publish
  • POST /api/Publish
Questions
  • Gets the questions in the survey. GET: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/Questions
  • Gets a question in the survey. GET: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/Questions/{questionId}
  • Updates a question in the survey. PUT: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/Questions/{questionId}
  • Deletes a question sub-tree in the survey, including all of its descendants. DELETE: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/Questions/{questionId}
  • Creates a single question in the survey. POST: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/Questions/New
  • Moves a set of questions in the survey. PUT: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/Questions/Move
  • Indents a set of questions in the survey. PUT: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/Questions/Indent
  • Unindents a set of questions in the survey. PUT: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/Questions/Unindent
  • Splits the question pages for a set of questions in the survey. PUT: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/Questions/Split
  • Merges the question pages for a set of questions in the survey. PUT: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/Questions/Merge
QuestionTemplates
  • Creates a new question template with the specified additional values. POST: api/QuestionTemplates/New
  • Gets the list of question template available for the current user. GET: api/QuestionTemplates
  • Gets the question template with the specified identifier. GET: api/QuestionTemplates/5
  • Updates a question template specified by its unique identfier and with the specified input values. PUT: api/QuestionTemplates/5
  • Delete a question template specified by its unique identfier . DELETE: api/QuestionTemplates/5
Resources
  • Get the list of resources in the survey. GET: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/Resources
  • Get a resource in the survey. GET: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/Resources/{resourceId}
  • Updates a resource in the survey. PUT: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/Resources/{resourceId}
  • Deletes a resource in the survey. DELETE: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/Resources/{resourceId}
  • Creates resources in the survey, one for each file uploaded in the request. POST: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/Resources
ResponseLinks
  • Gets all the response link of a specified question from a given survey with the specified identifiers. GET: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/Questions/1/ResponseLinks?SourceQuestionId=2
  • Updates a list of response link of a specified question from a given survey with the specified identidiers and input values. PUT: api/Surveys/5/Questions/1/ResponseLinks?SourceQuestionId=2
  • Gets the response link of a specified question from a guven survey with the specified identifiers. GET: api/Surveys/5/Questions/1/ResponseLinks/4?SourceQuestionId=2
  • Updates a response link of a specified question from a given survey with the specified identidiers and input values. PUT: api/Surveys/5/Questions/1/ResponseLinks/4?SourceQuestionId=2
Responses
  • Gets the responses in the question. GET: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/Questions/{questionId}/Responses
  • Updates multiple responses in the survey. PUT: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/Questions/{questionId}/Responses
  • Creates multiple responses in the survey question. POST: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/Questions/{questionId}/Responses
  • Deletes a set of responses in the survey. DELETE: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/Questions/{questionId}/Responses
  • Gets a response in the survey. GET: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/Questions/{questionId}/Responses/{responseId}
  • Updates a response in the survey. PUT: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/Questions/{questionId}/Responses/{responseId}
  • Deletes a response in the survey. DELETE: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/Questions/{questionId}/Responses/{responseId}
  • Creates a single response in the survey question. POST: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/Questions/{questionId}/Responses/New
  • Moves a responses in the question. PUT: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/Questions/{questionId}/Responses/Move
  • Indents a set of responses in the survey. PUT: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/Questions/{questionId}/Responses/Indent
  • Unindents a set of responses in the survey. PUT: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/Questions/{questionId}/Responses/Unindent
Routings
  • Gets the routings in the survey. GET: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/Routings
  • Updates routings in a given survey. PUT: api/Surveys/5/Routings
  • Creates new routings in a given survey. POST: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/Routings
  • Delete a set of routings from a given survey by specifying by their unique identfiers. DELETE: api/Surveys/5/Routings
  • Gets a routing in the survey. GET: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/Routings/{routingId}
  • Updates a routing from a given survey by specifying by its unique identfier and with the specified input values. PUT: api/Surveys/5/Routings/2
  • Delete a routing from a given survey by specifying by its unique identfier. DELETE: api/Surveys/5/Routings/2
  • Gets the result of compiling a routing. GET: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/Routings/{routingId}/Compile
  • Gets the result of compiling a script without needing a routing. GET: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/Routings/Compile
  • Converts an assisted script to advanced without needing a routing. GET: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/Routings/AssistedScriptToAdvanced
  • Converts an advanced script to assisted without needing a routing. GET: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/Routings/AdvandcedScriptToAssisted
  • Creates a new routing in a given survey. POST: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/routings/New
  • Delete targets for a routing from a given survey. DELETE: api/Surveys/5/Routings/2/Targets
  • Moves a set of routings in the survey. PUT: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/Routings/Move
ScenarioEntities
  • Gets all the scenario entities with the specified identifiers. GET: api/Surveys/5/ScenarioEntities
  • Creates multiple scenario entities with the specified input values. POST: api/Surveys/5/ScenarioEntities
  • Deletes multiple scenario entities with the specified identifiers. DELETE: api/Surveys/5/ScenarioEntities
  • GET /api/Surveys/{surveyId}/ScenarioEntities/{scenarioId}
  • Deletes a scenario entity with the specified identifiers. DELETE: api/Surveys/5/ScenarioEntities/2
  • Creates a scenario entity with the specified identidiers and input values. POST: api/Surveys/5/ScenarioEntities/New
Scenarios
  • Gets the scenarios in the survey. GET: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/Scenarios
  • Delete multiple scenarios from a given survey. DELETE: api/Surveys/5/Scenarios
  • Gets the scenario from a given survey with the specified identifier. GET: api/Surveys/5/Scenarios/2
  • Updates a scenario from a given survey by specifying by its unique identfier and with the specified input values. PUT: api/Surveys/5/Scenarios/2
  • Delete a scenario from a given survey by specifying by its unique identfier. DELETE: api/Surveys/5/Scenarios/2
  • Creates a new scenario to a given survey with the specified additional values. POST: api/Surveys/{surveyId}/Scenarios/New
Surveys
  • Creates a new survey with the specified additional values. POST: api/Surveys/New
  • Creates a survey from with the specified AskiaCore survey template unique identifier. POST: api/Surveys/CreateFromSurveyTemplate/5
  • Gets the texts of a survey. GET: api/Surveys/5/Texts -&gt; returns texts in all languages of the survey GET: api/Surveys/5/Texts?languageIds=1036,2057 -&gt; returns texts for only the specified languages of the survey
  • Sets the texts of a survey. GET: api/Surveys/5/Texts -&gt; sets texts of the survey using the supplied CSV file
  • Gets the list of surveys available for the current user. GET: api/Surveys
  • Gets the survey with the specified identifier. GET: api/Surveys/5
  • Updates a survey specified by its unique identfier and with the specified input values. PUT: api/Surveys/5
  • Delete a survey specified by its unique identfier . DELETE: api/Surveys/5
SurveyTemplates
  • Creates a new survey template with the specified additional values. POST: api/SurveyTemplates/New
  • Gets the list of survey templates available for the current user. GET: api/SurveyTemplates
  • Gets the survey template with the specified identifier. GET: api/SurveyTemplates/5
  • Updates a survey template specified by its unique identfier and with the specified input values. PUT: api/SurveyTemplates/5
  • Delete a survey template specified by its unique identfier . DELETE: api/SurveyTemplates/5
Test
  • GET /api/Test/Survey/{surveyId}
  • POST /api/Test/Survey/{surveyId}
Themes
  • Get the list of themes available by the current user. GET: api/Themes

Schema Definitions

ControlDto: object

allowedQuestionTypes: integer[]

Specifies a list of the AskiaCore.QuestionType values identifying the types of questions that the control is valid for.

id: integer (int32)

Specifies the unique identifier of the extenstion.

name: string

Specifies the name of the extension.

properties: object[]

Specifies a list of AskiaDesign ExtensionProperty associated with this AskiaDesign Extension.

Example
{
  "allowedQuestionTypes": [
    "integer (int32)"
  ],
  "id": "integer (int32)",
  "name": "string",
  "properties": [
    {
      "defaultValue": "string",
      "description": "string",
      "group": "string",
      "id": "string",
      "name": "string",
      "options": [
        {
          "text": "string",
          "value": "string"
        }
      ],
      "type": "string"
    }
  ]
}

ExtensionPropertyDto: object

defaultValue: string

Specifies the default value of the ExtensionProperty.

description: string

Specifies a textual description of the ExtensionProperty.

group: string

Specifies to which group the ExtensionProperty belongs to.

id: string

Specifies the unique identifier of the ExtensionProperty.

name: string

Specifies the name of the ExtensionProperty.

options: object[]

Specifies the options of the property if the ExtensionProperty type is a list.

type: string

Specifies the type of the ExtensionProperty.

Example
{
  "defaultValue": "string",
  "description": "string",
  "group": "string",
  "id": "string",
  "name": "string",
  "options": [
    {
      "text": "string",
      "value": "string"
    }
  ],
  "type": "string"
}

ExtensionPropertyOptionDto: object

text: string

Specifies AskiaDesign ExtensionPropertyOption display name.

value: string

Specifies AskiaDesign ExtensionPropertyOption value field.

Example
{
  "text": "string",
  "value": "string"
}

message: string

{
  "code": "integer (int32)",
  "defaultMessage": "string",
  "key": "string",
  "message": "string"

afterEnd: string

CSS classes.

Properties of the extension (ADC / ADP) associated with the element. Default values are replaced with any custom values set for the element.
